<br>
Aye, SU3 rocks, especially with the large number of undead boss mobs in Luclin.  In SoV, it's 100% useless.  The question will be how much of PoP will be undead?  How much of the old world is?  RoK has 3 zones with some nice undead, but 0 boss mobs that are.  It's great for xp, solo.  It's great for Luclin boss mobs.  But that's it.  I'd rather have an ability that ups my damage 10% vs everything.  I'd much rather have the equiv of ambidexterity for 2h weapons.  It annoys me greatly with my paladin that my greatest weakness, damage dealing, is something my AA only helps with against 1 type of mob, while classes that already significantly outdamage me get a nice boost vs anything.  Then there's flurry as well, a further bit of damage increase for warriors vs everything.  General stuff is good.  Slower xp with them, since you can't choose to maximize the xp gained, but the freedom to go beat up anything you want on a given day.  <br>
<br>
Ask yourself seriously which you'd rather want: 10% vs all or 20% vs undead?<br>
<br>
I do hope they fix some stuff in PoP.  It sounds like they'll need to address the hp vs mitigation issue.  With monks getting high AC/HP stuff, warriors (and paladins/sks) need to catch up to the monks in mitigation.  Warrior damage is fine, as long as boss mobs have reasonable AC.  But taunt/aggro needs work.  An AA skill that works the reverse of the casters aggro reduction would would be awesome.  It would still mean paladins/sks taunt better, on demand, but warrior aggro will increase a lot.  The impact of 5-10% can be seen quite easily with the enchanter aggro mods.  1 class only gear is something Verant is trying to get away from.  But something that gives warriors a bigger benefit from pure hp things (+hp spells like aego, symbol, brell's, and focus and +hp on gear) would be nice, to distance the warriors and non-warriors a bit more.  These things are static to all classes right now, meaning that the better these get, the less, percentagewise, the gap between warriors and others.  A 10% bonus there and you tack on another 400+ hp to warriors.  <br>
<br>
As always though, balance is such a fine line.  If things were perfectly balanced, uber-guilds would have an equal mix of all classes.  But they aren't and they never have been.  There will always be some that rock, some that are in the middle, and some that suck.  There will be some that are &quot;needed&quot; in numbers (in quotes because 1 class is needed in numbers, others are wanted in numbers), some that suffer a very steep loss of effectiveness for each additional one added.  It's a tough thing to balance, especially with all the things that factor in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uparvvardt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Parv Vardt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/8/02 8:59:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=102>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Blah!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> For example warriors have 100 mitigation (hypothetical number)<br>
<br>
Paladins have 80 mitigation<br>
<br>
Additing 10 percent to warrior mitigation yields an additional 10 points<br>
<br>
Adding 10 percent to paladin mitigation adds 8 points.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Right.  And 80% of 110 is 88, so with this 10% upgrade, you're still 80% a warrior in mitigation.  With the added 2%, all you're doing is creating a static gap in mitigation, the effects of which are amplified with increases to either class.  I fail to see how such simple math evades people.  That, or VI can't explain properly what they want.<br>
<br>
The warrior class is being heavily marginalized with nothing being offered in return.  We're being defined primarily by our gear, and unless you have top quality gear you're not going to have any significant gains over other melee classes.  Skill at managing agro will only get you so far, and then it's up to having a shitload of good gear to carry you the rest of the way. <p><FONT FACE="verdana, arial" size="-2"><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66788">Parv Vardt</A> [<A HREF="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/">Legacy of Steel</A>]<BR>
