Paladins get Slay Undead instead of &quot;bracketed melee boost&quot; because it makes RP sense.  You are HOLY KNIGHTS, the bane of the undead.  Saying that :<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  It's great for xp, solo. It's great for Luclin boss mobs. But that's it <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Is like saying &quot;Ya, I can only use this half the time i raid, and then all the time I xp, but it really sucks&quot;.  Seriously, how many paladins with SU3 are screwing around in kunark? How many are spending any more time on velious than their ToV cycle and AoW?  You can XP in multiple zone with it, to great benefit.  It is of marginal use on boss mob encounters that a paladin would be participating in when he was at that level.  To me, it seems like a fine skill, and downplaying it because it only works on undead is bullshit.  Howling stones, Karnors basement, some seb, the grey, and probably a few others i'm too tired to think of right now are all blue at 60, and as such, are viable XP grinding spots.  What is the warrior equivilent of this?  Flurry? Heh.<br>
<br>
And lets be realistic, warriors aren't really bitching about their damage output compared to yours, we just want to TANK better than you, and better than everyone else, like it should be.  I think it's great that pallies get slay undead.  Very in character.  I just don't think that overall, the melees are balanced anymore, this time in the opposite direction.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/9/02 3:15:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=104>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_die.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Blah!</span><hr size=1> &gt;&gt;To me, it seems like a fine skill, and downplaying it because it only works on undead is bullshit. Howling stones, Karnors basement, some seb, the grey, and probably a few others i'm too tired to think of right now are all blue at 60, and as such, are viable XP grinding spots.<br>
