I've never said it wasn't a fine skill.  But people here are trying to make it out to be the second coming.  It isn't, it's got serious drawbacks that overall make it less useful than a 10% increase in damage vs anything.  Sure, you can do all those zones.  But it's all undead.  And those zones are pretty much solo/duo.  It gets old.  Fast.  But you'll primarily use those zones anyway (even before you have SU), simply because paladin damage sucks vs non-undead.  I'm not denying it's a great ability.  It is.  It gives a paladin with mass AA the ability to make xp needed to get other AA.  Of course, for the cost of SU3, he could have gotten the other useful AA stuff<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Huge investment to get SU3, after all.  Cost of things doesn't really matter though.  What matters is what you can do with everything in the end.  Higher cost can always be compensated for with more time.  Right now, with the large number of Luclin high end mobs being undead, it's sweet, if your guild does those mobs.  But if your guild doesn't, then it's not nearly that great.<br>
<br>
Anyway, as I said already, I'm not denying it's a good ability.  But ambidexterity is as good/better.  Right now, I see a bunch of people saying &quot;look, the grass is greener over there&quot;.   It isn't, it's the same shade of green.  Got to look at the complete picture, not just little snippets.<br>
